    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL pointer dereference in getCxt() when accessing F1AP instances\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP module was experiencing segmentation faults when attempting to access F1AP context instances other than instance 0. This occurred due to overly restrictive assertions in the `getCxt()`, `createF1inst()`, and `destroyF1inst()` functions that prevented proper multi-instance support.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when running in split-CU/DU configurations where different instance IDs were being passed to these functions, causing immediate crashes with \"assertion 'instanceP == 0' failed\" messages.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.c`: Removed restrictive DevAssert checks and added proper bounds checking against NUMBER_OF_gNB_MAX\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.c`: Updated all three functions to handle instance indices properly within array bounds\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.c`: Made instance parameter handling consistent across all F1AP context management functions\n\n"
}